Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.98,0:01:50.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Towels, towels!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.41,0:01:54.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A little more and we'd be super-sopping wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.08,0:01:57.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather lady was right! Thunderstorms this afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.66,0:01:59.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Uncle Mouri?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.72,0:02:02.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's on a work trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.39,0:02:06.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's a message on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.66,0:02:09.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now. Don't go touching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:12.27,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}You have one message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.27,0:02:13.60,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:18.64,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hello, this is Aki Asano from Nichiuri TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.64,0:02:22.68,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}I'm calling because I need to speak with you about something urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:26.28,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}You appear to be out, so I'll call again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.28,0:02:28.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Aki Asano?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.15,0:02:33.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather lady! You know,\Nshe does the weather on Nichiuri TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:36.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! She's on "News City" too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.83,0:02:41.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's super cool! I'm a big fan of hers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.33,0:02:45.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what could she urgently need to talk to him about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.50,0:02:51.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's talk with her instead,\Nas the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.74,0:02:53.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.21,0:02:54.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.92,0:02:57.63,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(320,360)}Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.38,0:02:58.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.76,0:03:02.72,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(320,316)}Aki Asano (27)\NWeather lady and newscaster
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.18,0:03:02.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you came all the way here in Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0}'s place?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.72,0:03:08.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! If you need help,\Nleave it to us, the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.26,0:03:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you greeting children today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:12.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:18.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Having to deal with kids just to gain popularity...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.52,0:03:19.44,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(400,400)\pos(300,340)}Kazumi Tsukumo (31)\NNewscaster
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:21.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Big-name newscasters sure have it tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:24.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yikes. What gaudy makeup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.21,0:03:25.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What's with that fingernail?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.98,0:03:27.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.98,0:03:34.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Behave yourselves, kiddies.\NDon't get in the way of her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.02,0:03:41.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unpleasant person!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.43,0:03:45.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she the person who did the news before you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We switched places\Nabout half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:54.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was she what you wanted to talk to Mr. Mouri about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.24,0:03:58.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. A-Actually, uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:02.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if Detective Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} would be on News City!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.58,0:04:06.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, what a downer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.38,0:04:09.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What a relief it wasn't a case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.52,0:04:12.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's that sound?\N- What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:14.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:18.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0} told me to take it\Nbecause I always suddenly disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:20.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:22.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a cell phone, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:25.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a receiver!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it broke, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.64,0:04:28.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. For the sake of justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.87,0:04:30.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.67,0:04:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the detective agency's number,\Nso it must be Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.85,0:04:40.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know! Could you give me your pager's number?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.22,0:04:43.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can contact you when I need the Detective Boys' help!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.62,0:04:46.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.02,0:04:49.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! It's written right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.36,0:04:51.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.66,0:04:57.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Now to save "Detective Boys" to my phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:05:01.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go! All done!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:07.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! This only shows numbers, huh?\NI used to have one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:11.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My friends and I often used numbers to write messages for fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:12.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:14.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it can only display numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:19.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you can use numbers that look and sound like letters to write things!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:24.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, "428" could be read "Shibuya"!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.86,0:05:28.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,4, 2, 8... Shi-bu-ya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.87,0:05:31.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibuya! Neat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.07,0:05:35.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, since you're here, how about a tour of the News City studio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.94,0:05:38.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes!\N- Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.08,0:05:40.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:43.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Asano.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.38,0:05:52.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes. I will. Yes. Okay. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.39,0:05:56.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I have work to do, so I can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.20,0:06:00.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Kobayashi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.50,0:06:08.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to ask, but could you show them to Studio A?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:10.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Some work just came up, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:11.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it's no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.74,0:06:14.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and could you get them some passes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:15.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.28,0:06:16.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:18.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:21.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.82,0:06:24.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How long is she going to make us wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:27.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to suddenly ask you to stand in like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:30.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine, but what's this\Nabout Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} being threatened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.13,0:06:31.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Threatened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.53,0:06:34.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are these kids?!\NThey're distracting! Get rid of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.87,0:06:36.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:42.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Running off because of a threat?!\NAki-{\i1}san{\i0} is a failure as a journalist!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.61,0:06:45.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're beginning rehearsal!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:51.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0} hates children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:55.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, she said Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:56.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.49,0:07:00.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to see Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}\Nin Detective Mouri's place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.36,0:07:02.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.43,0:07:05.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Well, just between us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.96,0:07:08.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s been getting harassing letters and phone calls
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.83,0:07:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,ever since she started a story about\Na certain politician's corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.97,0:07:15.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She got a letter this morning threatening to kill her
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:18.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if she appeared on today's News City.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.44,0:07:23.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Was this threat what she really wanted to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:27.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the News City broadcast on that TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.12,0:07:30.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have work to do, so I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.79,0:07:37.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you think the phone call Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} got earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.13,0:07:39.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was a threatening phone call?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:42.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and then that scared her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.43,0:07:45.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} isn't a weakling like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.74,0:07:48.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You agree with me, right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.57,0:07:51.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.51,0:07:57.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}When she was on the phone then,\Nshe didn't seem afraid at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.25,0:08:02.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}In fact, she sounded happy,\Nas if she had gotten a special scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:05.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}That call was probably not a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.82,0:08:11.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}No, wait! If that call had been\Na trap to lure her somewhere—!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:17.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Ran-{\i1}oneechan{\i0} again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.63,0:08:19.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.50,0:08:24.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}. Only she and Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0} know this number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.88,0:08:26.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:36.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hello, this is Asano. I'm not home right now, so please leave your—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:38.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why'd you hang up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.72,0:08:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.92,0:08:45.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was her home. But it was her answering machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.93,0:08:50.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd! Why would she have you call her home if she isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.87,0:08:57.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,1-1-0?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:08:58.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,110—the police emergency number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.48,0:09:01.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.14,0:09:03.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the police call us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.21,0:09:05.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It's Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.48,0:09:11.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bad guy must've caught her!\NSo she wants us to call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.29,0:09:15.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then couldn't she just call them herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.49,0:09:19.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she's unable to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.57,0:09:25.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.84,0:09:28.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an abduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.58,0:09:33.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9109.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.64,0:09:37.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the city code of her phone number!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.51,0:09:42.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police won't listen to us with only this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.02,0:09:47.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the police can't help,\Nthen the Detective Boys will!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:52.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But this isn't enough to know where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:53.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.41,0:09:54.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.23,0:09:57.20,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}And now for today's sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.20,0:10:02.27,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The J-League game at the National Stadium between the Tokyo—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.27,0:10:05.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I like Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} a lot better...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:10.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,2003.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:14.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it! It's read "temple guardian"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:14.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(410,432)\blur2\fs24}niou-sama
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:17.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's where there are temple guardian statues!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.62,0:10:20.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Come on. Can't you deduce a little better than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.79,0:11:00.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The messages after 7:20 make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.20,0:11:05.57,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Lastly, we've just received this news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.57,0:11:08.57,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}The Special Investigation Unit of the Tokyo Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.57,0:11:11.58,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}is to question the politicians\NMr. Maruya and Mr. Okubo tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.58,0:11:13.58,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}about their possible acceptance of large bribes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.58,0:11:17.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}in relation to the corruption case\Ninvolving Bay Development.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.42,0:11:21.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out what Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s messages mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.62,0:11:23.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For reals, Mitsuhiko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:28.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These are indicating the names of the politicians who took bribes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.29,0:11:31.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,0 is "maru". Maruya's initial, basically!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:35.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,00 is "oo." Okubo's initial!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.03,0:11:38.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the 96 of 096 is "kuro"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.03,0:11:45.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} is trying to say it's Maruya who's guilty of corruption!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:48.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do 2003 and 5656 mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:54.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're bank account numbers used for the bribes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:11:59.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} must be captured at Maruya's home then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.96,0:12:01.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry and save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:06.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he lives in West Teitan, one subway stop from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:09.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.97,0:12:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.87,0:12:19.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's thunder! Let's run, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.08,0:12:28.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}"Maruya"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.92,0:12:33.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan! Hurry up! Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:36.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep watch for anyone coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:38.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko! Hurry up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:40.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.03,0:12:45.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.30,0:12:47.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.07,0:12:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.71,0:12:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't believe you guys ran off without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.85,0:13:01.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we'll have to do something about the guard and the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.48,0:13:04.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- You saw them first!\N- Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:09.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:11.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:12.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.67,0:13:13.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go call her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.80,0:13:21.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, it's raining again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.74,0:13:23.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.67,0:13:25.24,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:27.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you at this time of night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.41,0:13:30.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I paged you and paged you, but you ignored me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.75,0:13:33.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry! I'll be home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:35.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You better come home quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.09,0:13:42.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's thunder where you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:45.93,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Yeah. It's really rainy and thundery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.93,0:13:50.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice weather here. The moon is really pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:54.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pouring here, so I don't think I'll be home for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:57.04,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Where are you right now, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.04,0:13:59.80,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Should I bring an umbrella and come get you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.11,0:14:02.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.78,0:14:08.65,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}What? Hello? Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?\NHey, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.65,0:14:10.72,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Now for tomorrow's weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:14.66,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}A cold front in the northern Kanto region will bring clouds and rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.66,0:14:19.25,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Southern Kanto will have clear skies.\NTomorrow's high temperature...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:27.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going back to the TV station!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.67,0:14:30.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.14,0:14:33.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Wait up!\N- You better explain, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.82,0:14:44.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Try reading 2003 on its side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.56,0:14:46.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On its side?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.56,0:14:48.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-O-O-N.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.76,0:14:52.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it! Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:54.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.87,0:14:57.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It spells "moon" in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:15:03.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the reason Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} sent this "2003" message first
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:06.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was because she wanted us to look up at the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.44,0:15:10.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The "2003" was displayed at 7:20 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:14.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, the moon was in the southeast then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't visible from Maruya's mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:20.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because of buildings to the southeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.79,0:15:25.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} isn't at Maruya's home, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:30.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. She's being held somewhere where she can see the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.27,0:15:33.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't enough to tell us where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.91,0:15:37.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she used numbers like weather symbols
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:41.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to indicate weather changes where she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.91,0:15:44.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,0 is the circle meaning fair weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,00 is the double-circle meaning cloudy weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.89,0:15:53.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,096 is a filled circle, meaning rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.62,0:15:57.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the 5656 at 8:31?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:16:00.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say the sound effect for thunder out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:02.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Goro-goro...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:02.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24\pos(272,432)}5
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:02.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24\pos(296,432)}6
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:02.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24\pos(330,432)}5
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:02.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24\pos(354,432)}6
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.97,0:16:07.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! 5656 was referring to thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.71,0:16:09.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.71,0:16:17.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's being held where there was\Nrain and thunder around 8:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.86,0:16:28.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Places with thunderstorms at 8:30 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.86,0:16:33.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the only one was the area around this TV station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.98,0:16:34.45,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(450,500)\pos(320,300)}Nichiuri TV\NNews Bureau — Meteorology Center
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.86,0:16:36.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,within a 1-kilometer radius!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.13,0:16:37.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a passing shower!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.40,0:16:38.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.90,0:16:44.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you thought!\NAki-{\i1}san{\i0} is somewhere in this area!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.71,0:16:46.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.35,0:16:52.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,0109... What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:55.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't 01 be the symbol for "clear weather"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.42,0:16:59.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's still cloudy here. It must mean something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.69,0:17:05.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet 0109 means, "I want to eat a huge eel box lunch!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.26,0:17:07.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, she's probably hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:10.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.14,0:17:13.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.24,0:17:22.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem?! It's not {\i1}that{\i0} funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:27.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry! That's not it! Nice work, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.12,0:17:30.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I know where Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:52.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The large prop room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.11,0:17:54.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's where we got separated from her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.95,0:17:58.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, it's the northernmost room on the first floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.42,0:17:59.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.28,0:18:00.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.68,0:18:03.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s in the large prop room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:09.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Genta said, you read the 0, 10, and 9 of that 0109 separately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.33,0:18:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,0, 10, 9?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:13.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O... to... ku?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.40,0:18:14.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Large prop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.40,0:18:14.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fs24}ōdōgu
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.37,0:18:17.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of rooms in TV stations\Nthat people rarely enter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.77,0:18:21.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the kidnapper works here, they could use one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.77,0:18:24.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you know who it is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:28.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, because Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} told us who!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.06,0:18:40.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,End of the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.53,0:18:45.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use running.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.33,0:18:47.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:49.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Give yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.27,0:18:53.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You called Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} here,\Nknocked her out with drugs or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.94,0:18:56.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and locked her in that back room
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.24,0:19:01.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make others think she had run away,\Nout of fear of that threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.15,0:19:08.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You tried to ruin her credibility\Nand have her kicked off News City!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.62,0:19:12.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} used her cell phone to\Nsend us messages about her location
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.62,0:19:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,by referencing weather changes\Nshe could see outside the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:22.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Except, there was one message\Nshe sent that I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.37,0:19:25.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9109.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.40,0:19:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This number came in after\Na message to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.44,0:19:37.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if it didn't indicate her location...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.51,0:19:39.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...it indicated her kidnapper's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.95,0:19:43.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no, you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.36,0:19:45.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:55.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the Detective Boys!\NThere's no getting away from us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.43,0:19:57.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:20:00.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Hang on! Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.84,0:20:10.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,9109 is separated as 9-10-9.\NChanged to kanji and read aloud...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.32,0:20:14.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,..."tsu-ku-mo."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.55,0:20:18.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be you, Kazumi Tsukumo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.29,0:20:21.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.50,0:20:29.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't stand it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.97,0:20:36.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,News City was my idea!\NIt was my show from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.41,0:20:42.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then they replaced me with someone younger, someone cuter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:47.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is serious business! This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:52.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then earn the spot back with actual skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.46,0:21:00.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However you rationalize it,\Na crime can't be justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.49,0:22:40.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes this afternoon's weather forecast!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.76,0:22:42.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.33,0:22:44.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.43,0:22:46.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.00,0:22:51.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you all so much for yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.77,0:22:55.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But only the Detective Boys could've realized
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.37,0:22:58.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that my messages were weather codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.74,0:23:03.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know it was Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.22,0:23:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When she tried to put me to sleep,\NI caught a glimpse of her nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.65,0:23:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! The nail art!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.79,0:23:17.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! The design reminded me of a weather map, so I remembered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.23,0:23:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you're snow pellets, Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.20,0:23:20.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Snow pellets?\N- See?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.48,0:23:26.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\bord0\shad0\fscx100\a10\pos(440,340)\c&H00&}Snow Pellets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.84,0:23:31.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! That image fits you perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.38,0:23:32.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.75,0:23:37.77,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hey, Genta. You're not just snow pellets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.08,0:23:43.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1700)\bord0\shad0\fscx100\pos(312,346)\c&H00&\fs24}"Hail"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.45,0:23:43.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1700)}Hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.04,0:24:08.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(134,100)\fnSegoe\fscx105\fs28\fsp1\shad0\bord0\alpha&H1F&}NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.40,0:23:57.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}She looks pretty anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.84,0:24:00.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Who is that man with the long hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.67,0:24:05.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Why would there be something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.00,0:24:08.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6\pos(320,52)}Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(316,123)\a2\fscx80\fscy80\fnDINk\c&HFFFFFF&\b0\fs36\bord0\shad0}The Mysterious Sniper Murder Case
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.07,0:24:14.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(316,253)\a6\fscx80\fscy80\fnDINk\c&HFFFFFF&\b0\fs36\bord0\shad0}(Part 1)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.07,0:24:19.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint: Spotlight
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:24.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(314,410)\1a&H1F&\fnSegoe\3c&H7F001F&\3a&H7F&\fscx100\bord2\shad0\fs28}Look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Next time, it's an original story!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.65,0:24:21.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.91,0:24:23.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What's "original"?
